Sentencas: In this study, a strontium doped lanthanum cobalt ferrite thin film with 30% Sr on A-site, denoted as La0.7Sr0.3Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta or LSCF-7328, is investigated before and after annealing at 800 degrees C under CO2 containing atmosphere for 9 h.
Titulo: Chemical characterization of surface precipitates in La0.7Sr0.3Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The formation of secondary phases on surface of post-annealed LSCF-7328 is observed using atomic force microscope (AFM) and scanning electron microscope (SEM).
Titulo: Chemical characterization of surface precipitates in La0.7Sr0.3Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The extent of Sr segregation at the film surface is monitored using the synchrotron-based total reflection Xray fluorescence (TXRF) technique.
Titulo: Chemical characterization of surface precipitates in La0.7Sr0.3Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The bonding environment of the secondary phases formed on the surface is investigated by synchrotron-based hard X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (HAXPES).
Titulo: Chemical characterization of surface precipitates in La0.7Sr0.3Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Scanning transmission electron microscopy (STEM) and related spectroscopy techniques are used for micro structural and quantitative elemental analyses of the secondary phases on surface.
Titulo: Chemical characterization of surface precipitates in La0.7Sr0.3Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These studies reveal that the secondary phases on surface consist of SrO covered with a capping layer of SrCO3.
Titulo: Chemical characterization of surface precipitates in La0.7Sr0.3Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The formation of Co-rich phases is observed on the surface of post-annealed LSCF-7328.
Titulo: Chemical characterization of surface precipitates in La0.7Sr0.3Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode material for solid oxide fuel cells
